annotation.TEXT: Science count: 1
What, again?! GAAAMMMEEE!!!
Oh, down here is a warp. Maybe there was meant to be a warp under that Boo ring, perhaps leading to a bonus area? I don't know.
Maybe I should rewind out of that, because that was blatantly unfair, but... I'll let the death stand this time.
I wonder why SMW was programmed for certain Boos to assume that big Mario is always standing, even if he's ducking...
Ow. I wonder why SMW wasn't programmed like SMB2 or SMB3 when it came to spikes. (In those games, touching the sides of spikes didn't hurt you.)
And, I continue to have good luck in the Boo cloud room, even though I don't like it. However, I believe there's another room that I hate more than that Boo cloud room now!
Happy Halloween! And, welcome back to COLLAB! Now, let's see how "Deadly" this "Cave" is...
What?! Where did that guy come from?
Aw, if I had known this music was gonna play here, I wouldn't have loitered around at the goal of the previous level last time. Oh, well. The music was identified last time, so that's cool.
Wow, really? There's nothing down there but pit? Well, that's why that was a "science", which I'll now rewind out of.
Well, the bubble didn't make me invisible this time, but I still want to kill it.
Well, now I can't get that coin, and getting across this pit will be tough!
Alright, up next is Haunted Home, and I'm going to guess that this level has two exits, based on the overworld paths that I'll eventually corrupt.
Demo count: 1
What? I can't kill this Thwimp with this shell? Aw, man. Then I don't care about the shell nearly as much anymore.
Oh, that was one of those custom blocks that I've seen in Touhou Mario, which bounce you and make a fire-breathing noise. However, this one didn't damage me.
That time, my shell became invisible. Oh, and after killing the bubble, a Boo pops out of nowhere behind me. Yeah, there's definitely a sprite memory setting issue with this room.
Yeah, I figured I was near the goal, so I wasn't worried about time. Huh, there were no Yoshi coins in this level, and I don't think there was a midpoint either.
Shut up, clock.

It only happens sometimes though, as you just saw how I wasn't stopped every single time there. Also, I don't think there are any cases of that happening in the original SMW, where I believe all 45° slopes that meet a flat ledge use the kind of ledge that you can jump through from below.

So, which of these two levels should I play next? Vote for either Living Death Mine or Spooky Walk, and we'll find out where I go next time! To be continued... And now, a half-minute montage with Yakety Sax!
Maybe if I block clone coin blocks enough times, I can reach 30 coins...
GAAAMMMEEE!!!
Argh! My mushroom got stuck above the ceiling there! I think the ceiling should be removed starting from the goalposts, so that power ups don't get lost like that.
Or, it could turn out that the goal's right there...
Okay, I made it. Now, let's try not to accidentally prematurely kill any more possibly vital duders...
There's the P-switch. But, I think I'll wait on the secret exit for the time being, and go for all of the Yoshi coins on this run, if I can.
Demo count: 3
Oh, sure. Now I can destroy a koopa shell that way when I'm not trying to. Also, it would help if I had enough height...
Umm... Nothing happened. I was expecting the overworld to become corrupted here. Well, either I wasn't in the level long enough, or I didn't make enough button inputs.
Got it!
Yes, just barely. I wonder how you're supposed to reach it normally, though? Maybe blocks appear when you use the yet-to-be-found P-switch there?
Ah, I believe I can block factory this multi-coin block!
Okay, at long last, I'm going to see what the next room is!
Okay, I think I'll destroy this shell now so that I don't accidentally kill that paraduder...
...And, whoops! The game just crashed! Well, that just happened...
Ah, there we go! We have overworld corruption!

Now, apparently, I've been told that the title demo recording hack was never removed after it was used to create the custom title demo, and this causes problems. What kinds of problems? Well, let me just hang around in this level until the timer reaches 1...
Okay, this mushroom undoes the damage I took from the spikes while trying to cross that pit earlier.
Hmm... Maybe I've gotten 30 coins by now? I'd better not get killed by another surprise block as I go to check!
Nuts. I'd try to block factory this multi-coin block if it wasn't obstructed on both sides.
Push!
Ow. I guess standing still here isn't a good idea.
Yeah, I hadn't gotten 30 coins yet. Also, these note blocks aren't ordinary note blocks.
Oh, d'oh. I think I have to hit the upper-left part of the bubble to kill it.
Well, there's the door. But, frying enemies does give me coins... Maybe I've reached 30 by now? Probably not, but I guess I'll check anyway.
Okay, now for that secret exit.
Okay, seriously, that wasn't even close. Just like with Boo rings, the Boo cloud always treats big Mario's hitbox as if he's standing up, even if he's ducking. (Slow-motion instant replay time!)
Wow, how did I not get hit there? Well, I don't think the solid-looking Boos' hitboxes become active until they start moving.
Huh. That 1-up mushroom was red. But, it was still a 1-up, which is what I was supposed to get.
I'm hoping for a power up or multi-coin block that I can clone...

Thankfully, I didn't get hit at all there. Yeah, when I'm small, the game treats my hitbox more fairly when it comes to those Boos. Also, I'll continue to hold my reserve power up until I reach the power up block.
Oh, but now I've gotta go through this Boo cloud room that I don't like again. I'm not going to use my reserve power up here, because I know I'll just lose it to hitbox dissonance.
Nothing in those turn blocks. Can I reach the Yoshi coin with a max speed jump from the left?

Okay, so what is the purpose of these coin blocks? If they're meant to cheaply kill me, get rid of them! If they're meant to assist me in reaching the 30-coin mark, get rid of them anyway, and replace the broken ? block at the beginning of the room with a multi-coin block.
I wonder why SMW wasn't programmed to have slopped lava kill enemies like flat lava does...
Why did I do that? I should've waited a couple seconds there. Well, there's the secret exit, and it's obvious what I'll need to find in order to reach it.
Oh, there are hidden coin blocks. Of course. Well, now I've gotta carefully maneuver around these Boos...
If it's button inputs that I need, then what if I spend 273 seconds holding the rapid-fire A button? (Also, I'll move a little to the right so that Boo won't come after me.)
That opens up a corrupted path to Living Death Mine. And now, ludicrous speed level revisit.
Okay, no more Boo cloud. Oh, I see that Yoshi coin up there, and I bet I can get it by spin jumping off of a Boo!
Space-time rewind count: 2
Facing to the right here should be safe. Alright, I'm going to cut to when the timer gets low.
And, Mario turned invisible due to a problem with one of the sprite settings involving that green bubble.
Come on...
Oh, I like this. Move faster, Booey!
However, I don't want to leave the overworld this badly messed up, so I'm now going to go back to the way things were at the start of the episode.
Seriously, why are those hidden blocks there?!
Okay, the Boos have stopped appearing. That's good.

And, that unlocks a corrupted path to Spooky Walk. Also, I searched Haunted Home some more off screen, and couldn't find any more Yoshi coins. I even tried avoiding all items in the first two rooms, but nothing new appeared, so it's not an item memory index problem. If I did miss any Yoshi coins that actually were there, let me know!

One thing that I sometimes find annoying in hacks is that if a 45-degree slope ends at a completely solid tile like right here, Mario will sometimes bump into that solid tile and briefly stop as he's running up the slope, killing his momentum.
Push!
Huh? Um, dude? Your ? block is broken. Was this intentional? Or was this block actually supposed to contain something?
YES! BLOCK FACTORYYY!!!
Demo count: 2
But, then why is that Boo ring positioned like that? Was the Boo ring meant to be several tiles higher than where it currently is or something?
Danged bubble must've made that Boo invisible instead of me...
Meh. I'm not going to bother trying to block factory this block. I got my fill for the time being earlier.
And Mario's become Mr. Invisible again. If I can destroy that bubble, I'll get rid of this issue.
What?! Seriously?! Why the heck was there an invisible coin block there?!
Happy Halloween! And, welcome back to COLLAB! Now, before I move on with the game, I'm going to show off something.
Geez, this is getting stupid.
BGM: Pom Gets Wifi - Battle Theme / RPG Maker 2003 - Field 4
Okay, I'm suspicious as to why that Boo ring is way down there. There's gotta be a secret down there. I'm going to perform a "science"...
Yeah, I saw that star block down there, but I don't think I've collected 30 coins in this level yet.
Argh, this Boo cloud...
Goal tape average so far: 250 / 6 = 41.667 stars each.
Sigh... Let's try this again...
Hmm... A trapped springboard. Captain Obvious dictates that I'll need a P-switch in order to bounce off of it.
Game crash count: 1
BGM: CUSTOM - Haunted Melody by grishnax (This music was also used in "A House".)
Oh, yeah. There's a glitch with these phasing Boos. If you travel far enough horizontally (I think more than half a screen) after they phase in, they won't harm you during that appearance.
Space-time rewind count: 1
Okay, that was lucky. The one time I get the cloning right was indeed on a power up block. Oh, what's this? Ooh, I believe this is the first time I've seen a fire flower in this hack!
Stupid Eerie...
Honestly, I do not like this room. Get me outta here!
Alright, now when the timer hits 1, I'm going to Start+Select out.
Okay, I've rewound to a point a few seconds before the game flatlined on me there, and I'll just Start+Select out now.

Appearing/disappearing Boos. Just great. And, I believe that, just like with the Boo cloud and the Boo ring, they'll always treat ducking big Mario's hitbox as if he's standing upright. I'll try to keep that in mind.
It's strange how this level starts with 274 seconds, by the way. Why not a standard 300?
Alright, that's enough of that.
Well, no blocks or anything appeared near that Yoshi coin, so I wonder how you'd reach it normally...
Goal tape average so far: 290 / 7 = 41.429 stars each.
Yay, this shell is in a good sprite slot to kill Thwomps! Better take good care of it!
Boing!
Well, let's move on.
Nope, I didn't get killed by another surprise block, but nope, I still hadn't gotten 30 coins yet either. (Maybe I should've fried that koopa to my left first.)
Huh. The shell didn't kill the Sparky on the way up, but it did on the way down. How odd... Also, I found my P-switch.
Alright, now I'll once again cut to when the timer gets low...
Space-time rewind count: 3
Yes, gimme all of the flowers!
